{{unbulleted list
|{{note|aaa|[a]}} About 12,300 men of which 1,800 were stationed in [[Narva|Narva]] with 297 [[artillery|artillery pieces]] and 10,537 (5,889 [[infantry|infantry]], 4,314 [[cavalry|cavalry]], 37 [[cannon|cannon]]s with 334 crew) assaulting the [[Russia|Russia]]ns.<ref name="kuvaja">Christer Kuvaja (2008), p.139</ref>
|{{note|bbb|[b]}} Up to 37,000 men of which 4,000 were deployed at the [[siege|siege]]-works with 125 artillery pieces and 33,000 (23,652 infantry, 9,000 cavalry, 70 cannons with 321 crew) facing the [[Sweden|Swedes]].<ref name="Höglund">Lars-Eric Höglund, Åke Sallnäs, Alexander Vespalov (2011). Great Northern War 1700 - 1721, II.</ref><ref name="Generalstaben">Generalstaben (1918-1919). Karl XII på slagfältet.</ref><ref name="Tacitus">[http://www.tacitus.nu/karoliner/slag/Narva/ryssar.htm Tacitus.nu, Örjan Martinsson. Russian force.]</ref>
|{{note|ccc|[c]}} Reports of 31 [[officer|officer]]s and 636 [[Private_(rank)|private]]s dead, 66 officers and 1,181 privates wounded.<ref name="Boris">Boris Grigorjev & Aleksandr Bespalov (2012). Kampen mot övermakten. Baltikums fall 1700-1710. pp. 38</ref> Another report claims almost 900 dead Swedish troops<ref name ="ullgren">Ullgren (2008), p.57</ref>
|{{note|ddd|[d]}} Almost the entire Russian force was either killed or captured during the battle (except for some 4,000 cavalry who managed to escape over the kamperholm bridge).<ref name="Svenska slag">Ericson (2003), p. 257</ref> 8,000 Russians were reported killed and another 1,000 drowned.<ref name="Boris"/> Over 20,000 were captured and disarmed but later set free and allowed march to Russia (except for 700 men [134 officers] who were set prisoners).<ref name="Boris"/><ref name="Nolan">Cathal J. Nolan (2008). Wars of the Age of Louis XIV, 1650-1715. pp. 313</ref><ref name="Hughes">Hughes, Lindsey. Russia in the Age of Peter the Great. — New Haven: Yale University Press, 1998. pp. 30.</ref> 23,000 out of initially 37,000 Russians managed to reach back to Russian land, estimating the Russian final casualties to about 14,000 either dead during the battle or the harsh march back to Russia.<ref name="Boris"/> The Swedes also seized 171 [[Colours,_standards_and_guidons|standards and banners]], 145 [[cannon|cannon]]s, 28 [[Mortar_(weapon)|mortars]] and four [[howitzer|howitzer]]s as well as 24,000 [[musket|musket]]s.<ref name ="ullgren"/><ref name="Stormakten">Olle Larsson, Stormaktens sista krig (2009) Lund, Historiska Media. pp. 99</ref>
}}{{hidden end}}

|campaignbox = {{Campaignbox 大北方戰爭}}
}}

'''纳尔瓦之役'''（{{lang-rus|Битва на Нарве}}，{{lang-sv|Slaget vid Narva}}，{{lang-en|Battle of Narva}}）发生于1700年11月30日，[[俄羅斯帝國|俄羅斯帝國]]入侵瑞典領土。最終[[瑞典国王|瑞典国王]][[卡爾十二世|卡爾十二世]]以一流的战术大败[[沙皇|沙皇]][[彼得大帝|彼得大帝]]的大军。這場戰役是[[大北方战争|大北方战争]]的開端。

11月30日，37,000名俄军包围了仅由8,140名瑞典军（由卡尔十二世率领）防守的[[纳尔瓦|纳尔瓦]]，但中午，查理十二世的瑞典军与援兵突袭俄军，轻易地把慌张的俄军打败，加上俄军指挥多是外地人，使很多军团都不能合作，所以战役后，俄军失去了足足15,000人，而瑞典则只有667人阵亡。

